The Minister of Information and Culture, Lai Mohammed says President Muhammadu Buhari’s achievements in office will last for many generations to come, noting that never in the history of Nigeria has any administration done so much with so little like the present administration.  Speaking during a press conference in Abuja to mark the second anniversary of the second term of the Buhari Administration, the Minister expressed disappointment on some groups or individuals whom he described as naysayers for not seeing all the efforts of the administration to better the lives of Nigerians.  The minister while highlighting the current administration's achievements, said  President Buhari has achieved so much despite the paucity of funds.  The minister however, acknowledged the security challenges facing the nation but maintained that President Buhari will not be deterred.